history.content: That seems like a pretty solid schedule. 170 psets can take some time each week. 186 and 161 mainly take time for projects (186 says they have homeworks, not projects, but they are projects), so plan around those

children.subject: both classes are a lot of work, and not only that, the project deadlines are always right around the same time.  mid-September to mid-November will be hell.  I wasn't intending on doing this combo, but I had a class cancel on me which would have made my life much less stressful.
just a question—how much work is 61b/61c concurrently? do you think it helps you learn the material better?

history.content:
how will it be from a workload standpoint?  Difficulty I'm not too worried about.

For reference, I'm now taking 61B, 61C, Data 100 and STAT 140, and the middle of the semester was vicious, but I can see the light at the end of the tunnel now, especially after this week.
